ACLs (87%). There was minimal difference in graft primary patency rates, and no 
difference in assisted primary patency, limb salvage, and survival rates between 
patients with and without APLs who underwent leg bypass grafting procedures. The 
extreme morbidity rate associated with APLs in previous reports is not confirmed 
by this prospective study. APLs should not be regarded as a contraindication to 
indicated leg bypass grafting procedures.

