(1)University of Michigan School of Medicine, Ann Arbor, USA.

The randomized angiotensin receptor antagonist--angiotensin converting enzyme 
(ACE)--Inhibitor Study (RAAS) was designed to test the hypothesis that the 
addition of an angiotensin II type 1 receptor blocking agent, losartan 50 
mg/day, to an ACE-inhibitor, enalapril 10 mg twice a day (group 1), will be more 
